SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
A session that begins with mild frustration but normalises quickly:
  1. Arrival — client mentions the wait and is mildly annoyed; worker apologises.
  2. Reset — worker redirects to the session agenda; client accepts.
  3. Substantive session — routine discussion of the client issue; normal tone.
  4. Minor snag — a small administrative issue arises; resolved cooperatively.
  5. Close — session ends productively; client is satisfied or at least accepting.
This is NOT a confusor — it is a true neutral. The mild frustration resolves before tension builds.

